<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Inter Milan enjoyed a high-scoring victory of 5-2 against Benevento in their second game of the 2020-2021 campaign. </p>

<p>Romelu Lukaku added two goals to his tally, while Benevento - who beat Sampdoria 3-2 in their first game back in the top flight - struggled to keep up their winning ways as they slipped back into their 2017-18 form.  </p>

<p>The hosts did, however, manage to put two past Antonio Conte's men.  </p>

<p>Inter Milan's first goal came in the opening minute of the game as Romelu Lukaku slotted home his first of the game.</p>

<p>Inter's next two goals from Roberto Gagliardin and Achraf Hakimi came in quick succession, with the first coming in the 25th minute and the second in the 28th minute. </p>

<p>Benevento clawed one back with a right footed shot from Gianluca Caprari that flew into the bottom left corner of the goal.  </p>

<p>Achraf Hakimi scored a right footed shot from the centre of the box to the bottom right corner in the 42nd minute of the game.  </p>

<p>Before Lautaro Martinez punished Benevento in the 71st minute after being assisted by Alexis Sanchez. </p>

<p>Benevento did, however, finish the game off well with Caprari picking up another goal. Gianluca Lapadula set Caprari up for a right footed shot from the centre of the box to the bottom left corner. </p>

<p>Benevento</p>

<p>TEAM: Montipo, Maggio, Glik, Caldirola, Barba, Ionita, Schiattarella, Dabo, Insigne, MoncinI, Caprari</p>

